# Implementation Plan: Chat Enhancements

This plan outlines the steps to implement real-time auto-refresh, typing indicators, and message history retention for both the mobile and web dashboard applications.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To implement a true "typing" indicator via HTTP polling without WebSockets, I will need to add a new `TypingStatus` table to the Django backend to temporarily track who is typing to whom. Please confirm this database schema change is acceptable.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (Django)
---
#### [NEW] [models.py](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/backend/api/models.py)
- Create a `TypingStatus` model with `user_id`, `chat_partner_id`, `is_typing`, and `updated_at`.

#### [MODIFY] [serializers.py](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/backend/api/serializers.py)
- Add a `TypingStatusSerializer`.

#### [MODIFY] [views.py](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/backend/api/views.py)
- Create `update_typing_status(request)` to accept POST requests when a user types.
- Create `get_typing_status(request)` to fetch the current typing state for a chat session.

#### [MODIFY] [urls.py](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/backend/api/urls.py)
- Add routes for `/api/typing/update/` and `/api/typing/status/`.

### Frontend (Flutter Mobile & Web Dashboard)
---
#### [MODIFY] [api_service.dart (Mobile)](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/mobile/lib/services/api_service.dart) & [api_service.dart (Dashboard)](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/dashboard/lib/services/api_service.dart)
- Add `updateTypingStatus(bool isTyping, String partnerId)` method.
- Add `getTypingStatus(String partnerId)` method.

#### [MODIFY] [messages_screen.dart (Mobile)](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/mobile/lib/screens/messages_screen.dart)
- Reduce the `_pollingTimer` interval from 15 seconds to 3 seconds for near real-time updates without WebSockets.
- Add an `onChanged` listener to `TextField` to trigger `updateTypingStatus(true)` with a debounce to revert to `false`.
- In the `_pollingTimer`, fetch both new messages *and* the typing status of the provider.
- Add a "Provider is typing..." UI element above the input field when active.

#### [MODIFY] [dashboard_screen.dart (Dashboard)](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/dashboard/lib/screens/dashboard_screen.dart)
- In the [_MessagePanelState](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/dashboard/lib/screens/dashboard_screen.dart#821-1040) drawer, implement a similar 3-second `Timer` to poll for messages and typing status.
- Add an `onChanged` listener to the text input to broadcast the provider's typing status.
- Show a "Patient is typing..." indicator.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- N/A

### Manual Verification
1. I will deploy the backend changes to Render and the dashboard to Firebase.
2. I will rebuild the Android APK.
3. You will open the Dashboard on your computer and the App on your phone.
4. When you start typing on the phone, the Dashboard should show "Patient is typing..." within 3 seconds.
5. When you send a message, it should appear on the other side within 3 seconds without having to refresh the page.
6. Opening a chat should immediately load the historical messages.
